infos.info: Personalities designated as ';Guest'; appeared at various times, most with music or bands. Arvell Shaw, Jay McShann, Jules Bledsoe, Lem Davis and Erroll Garner are not mentioned in Dunning's Encyclopedia. - Jubilee was transcribed by the Special Services Division of the War Department until 1943, then by Armed Forces Radio Service. Michael Perriere conducted the AFRS orchestra after 1945.Program was distributed to service personnel and was not heard at home. (Dunning)
